9 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Prohibition on access to child sexual abuse material. (1) A content
10 provider who produces, publishes, distributes, or maintains a substantial amount of sexually explicit visual
11 content IN A MANNER IN WHICH THE VISUAL CONTENT IS REASONABLY ACCESSIBLE IN MONTANA may not produce,
12 publish, distribute, or maintain child sexual abuse material in a manner in which the material is reasonably
13 accessible in Montana.
14 (2) A content provider may not collect revenue or make a profit from distributing child sexual abuse
15 material to an individual A PERSON physically located in Montana, regardless of whether the material is produced
16 or created by a third party or regardless of how the revenue is generated.
17 (3) A CONTENT PROVIDER WHO GENERATES 50% OR MORE OF THE CONTENT PROVIDER'S INCOME FROM
18 THE PRODUCTION, PUBLICATION, OR DISTRIBUTION OF SEXUALLY EXPLICIT VISUAL CONTENT AND WHO HAS GENERATED
19 AT LEAST $500,000 IN INCOME MAY NOT PRODUCE, PUBLISH, DISTRIBUTE, OR MAINTAIN CHILD SEXUAL ABUSE MATERIAL
20 IN A MANNER IN WHICH THE MATERIAL IS REASONABLY ACCESSIBLE IN MONTANA.
21 (3)(4) In an action filed under [section 3] alleging a violation of this section, it is a defense that a
22 content provider removes visual content that contains child sexual abuse material within 48 96 hours of the
23 visual content being made reasonably accessible in Montana.
24 (5) IN AN ACTION FILED UNDER [SECTION 3] ALLEGING A VIOLATION OF THIS SECTION, IT IS A DEFENSE THAT
25 THE PERSON MAINTAINING AN ACTION TO SEEK REMEDIES AVAILABLE UNDER [SECTION 4] CAUSED THE ALLEGED
26 VIOLATION OF THIS SECTION TO OCCUR BY UPLOADING OR OTHERWISE CAUSING THE CHILD SEXUAL ABUSE MATERIAL TO
27 BE PRODUCED, PUBLISHED, DISTRIBUTED, OR MAINTAINED BY THE CONTENT PROVIDER.
