10 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Enforcement -- right of victim to bring action -- enforcement by
11 department of justice -- private right of action -- statute of limitations. (1) A person VICTIM, OR THE PARENT
12 OR GUARDIAN OF A VICTIM IF THE VICTIM IS CURRENTLY UNDER 18 YEARS OF AGE, DEPICTED IN CHILD SEXUAL ABUSE
13 MATERIAL THAT IS ACCESSED who is injured by a IN violation of [section 2] may maintain an action to seek the
14 remedies available under [section 4] as well as restitution FOR A VIOLATION OF [SECTION 2].
15 (2) The department has the authority to enforce [section 2] and may maintain an action to seek the
16 remedies available under [section 4]. The department shall serve a copy of the complaint on a victim who is
17 harmed by the violation alleged in the complaint if the identity of the victim can be reasonably ascertained.
18 (3)(2) For any violation of [section 2] not prosecuted by the victim under the authority in subsection
19 (1) or the department under the authority in subsection (2), a private person may maintain an action to seek the
20 remedies under [section 4].The PRIVATE person shall serve a copy of the complaint on a victim who is harmed
21 by the violation alleged in the complaint if the identity of the victim can be reasonably ascertained.
22 (4)(3) An action under subsection (1) or (2) must be brought within 50 15 2 years of the violation.
23 (5)(4) An action under subsection (2) or (3) must be brought within 40 10 years of the violation.
